  "doc_id": "44168",
  "text": "Subjects: Patients with dementia and controls pair-matched for age (±2 years), sex and location were recruited from the clinics and day-hospitals of a geriatric and a psychogeriatric unit. Patients referred specifically because of mobility problems or falls, and those who were bed-or chair-bound, had a history of stroke or Parkinson's disease, a Hachinski Ischaemic Score more than 4 [CITATION_1] , had been treated with neuroleptic medications within the previous year or had musculoskeletal, neuropathic or spastic causes of gait disturbance were excluded.",
