      "span_text": "Patients referred specifically because of mobility problems or falls, and those who were bed-or chair-bound, had a history of stroke or Parkinson's disease, a Hachinski Ischaemic Score more than 4  , had been treated with neuroleptic medications within the previous year or had musculoskeletal, neuropathic or spastic causes of gait disturbance were excluded.",
